Hills Department Stores Inc said ithas decided to amend the registration on file with theSecurities and Exchange Commission covering its planned initialoffering.    The company said it expects to offer three mln commonshares at a filing range of 11 to 12 dlrs a share along with a40 mln dlr offering of convertible junior subordinateddebentures instead of the 6.9 mln common shares proposed in thepending registration.    Hills said it expects to file a registration statement onthe proposed changes within two weeks. Reuter&#3;